.TH "rocket-sync-tracker" "1" "2024-03-13" "Rocket Sync-Tracker User Manual" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
rocket-sync-tracker - sync-tracker editor for demoscene productions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]rocket-sync-tracker\f[R] [\f[I]FILE\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]Rocket\f[R] is a sync-tracker, a tool for synchronizing music and
visuals in demoscene productions.
It provides a Qt5-based GUI editor and an ANSI C client library
(\f[B]librocket\f[R]) that can either communicate with the editor over a
network socket during development, or play back an exported data-set in
the final release.
.PP
The editor is laid out like a music-tracker: tracks (columns) hold named
variables; rows represent discrete points in time.
Key-frames can be set at any row; Rocket interpolates between adjacent
key-frames according to a per-key-frame interpolation mode.
.PP
If \f[I]FILE\f[R] is provided, the specified \f[B].rocket\f[R] project
file is opened on startup.
.SH INTERPOLATION MODES
.TP
\f[B]Step\f[R]
Always returns the exact value of the key-frame (no interpolation).
.TP
\f[B]Linear\f[R]
Linearly interpolates between the current and the next key-frame value.
.TP
\f[B]Smooth\f[R]
Applies a smooth-step (S-curve) interpolation between two values.
.TP
\f[B]Ramp\f[R]
Like Linear, with an additional exponentiation applied to the
interpolation factor.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
\f[B]Up\f[R]/\f[B]Down\f[R]/\f[B]Left\f[R]/\f[B]Right\f[R]
Move the cursor.
.TP
\f[B]PgUp\f[R]/\f[B]PgDn\f[R]
Move the cursor 16 rows up or down.
.TP
\f[B]Home\f[R]/\f[B]End\f[R]
Move the cursor to the beginning or end of the track.
.TP
\f[B]Ctrl+Left\f[R]/\f[B]Ctrl+Right\f[R]
Move the current track left or right.
.TP
\f[B]Enter\f[R]
Enter a key-frame value at the cursor position.
.TP
\f[B]Del\f[R]
Delete the key-frame at the cursor position.
.TP
\f[B]i\f[R]
Cycle through interpolation modes.
.TP
\f[B]k\f[R]
Toggle a bookmark on the current row.
.TP
\f[B]Alt+PgUp\f[R]/\f[B]Alt+PgDn\f[R]
Jump to the previous or next bookmarked row.
.TP
\f[B]Space\f[R]
Pause or resume demo playback.
.TP
\f[B]Shift+Up\f[R]/\f[B]Down\f[R]/\f[B]Left\f[R]/\f[B]Right\f[R]
Extend the selection.
.TP
\f[B]Ctrl+C\f[R]
Copy the selection.
.TP
\f[B]Ctrl+V\f[R]
Paste.
.TP
\f[B]Ctrl+Z\f[R]
Undo.
.TP
\f[B]Shift+Ctrl+Z\f[R]
Redo.
.TP
\f[B]Ctrl+B\f[R]
Bias (offset) the selected key-frames.
.TP
\f[B]Shift+Ctrl+Up\f[R]/\f[B]Shift+Ctrl+Down\f[R]
Quick-bias the selection by ±0.1.
.TP
\f[B]Ctrl+Up\f[R]/\f[B]Ctrl+Down\f[R]
Quick-bias the selection by ±1.
.TP
\f[B]Ctrl+PgUp\f[R]/\f[B]Ctrl+PgDn\f[R]
Quick-bias the selection by ±10.
.TP
\f[B]Shift+Ctrl+PgUp\f[R]/\f[B]Shift+Ctrl+PgDn\f[R]
Quick-bias the selection by ±100.
.SH FILES
.TP
*\f[B].rocket\f[R]
Project file containing all tracks and key-frames for a production.
.TP
\f[B]\[ti]/.config/rocket/\f[R]
Per-user Qt application settings.
.SH NOTES
.PP
During development, \f[B]rocket-sync-tracker\f[R] listens on TCP port
\f[B]1338\f[R] (default) for incoming connections from a demo client
linked against \f[B]librocket\f[R].
All edits made in the editor are mirrored to the demo client in real
time.
For the final release, the demo is compiled with the
\f[B]SYNC_PLAYER\f[R] preprocessor symbol defined, and plays back the
data-set previously exported from the editor.
.SH BUGS
.PP
Report bugs at: <https://github.com/rocket/rocket/issues>
.PP
Or to the Rocket mailing list: <rocket-dev@googlegroups.com>
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
The full documentation and examples are available in
\f[B]/usr/share/doc/rocket-sync-tracker/\f[R].
